  "content": "       </div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);\">Insta360 X5</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 17px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); margin-top: 4px;\">360° underwater footage</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <!-- Pipeline -->\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n      <span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--accent-cyan); font-weight: 600;\">footage</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">- - →</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--accent-cyan); font-weight: 600;\">AI</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">- - →</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--accent-cyan); font-weight: 600;\">timeline</span>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.5; text-align: center;\">\n      I love editing, but the repetitive parts eat time I'd rather spend diving.<br>\n      Found a <span style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan); font-weight: 600;\">DaVinci Resolve MCP</span>. Still brainstorming.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"author-tag\" style=\"color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\" style=\"color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);\">06 / 07</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- Slide 7: TAKEAWAYS -->\n<div class=\"slide closing\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">Key Takeaways</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">What I Learned Setting Up <span class=\"highlight\">Resolve</span> on Linux</div>\n\n  <div style=\"flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; gap: 0;\">\n\n    <!-- Takeaway 1 -->\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: flex-start; padding: 28px 32px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 36px; flex-shrink: 0;\">🔍</div>\n      <div style=\"min-width: 0;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 8px;\">Error messages lie.</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;\">The GPU error pointed at memory. The real cause was the display server. Always read the logs.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>",
